verb.description: To leap over, beyond, or across. Chiefly poetic.
To surpass or excel in leaping; to leap higher or further than.

origin: Old English (in an earlier sense). Cognate with or formed similarly to Middle Dutch utelopen (Dutch uitloopen), Middle Low German ūtlopen, Middle High German ūzloufen (German auslaufen) from the Germanic base of out- + the Germanic base of leap. Compare to leap out.
